athyper-api-runtime.name: base:operator
athyper-api-runtime.description: Execute workflows + all viewer permissions

athyper-api-runtime.name: base:viewer
athyper-api-runtime.description: Read-only access to core entities, workflows, documents, and content

athyper-api-runtime.name: runtime:read
athyper-api-runtime.description:
Grants read-only access to core runtime entities (metadata, state, configurations, execution logs).
Use cases:
View entity details; Fetch lifecycle state; Query runtime status dashboards

athyper-api-runtime.name: mod:PAY:user
athyper-api-runtime.description: Payments module user (operator-level)

athyper-api-runtime.name: svc:bff
athyper-api-runtime.description: BFF service account composite — invoke + doc/content access

athyper-api-runtime.name: wf:approval:execute
athyper-api-runtime.description: Execute approval engine decisions including rule evaluation and multi-level approvals. Use cases: Auto-approval rules; Policy-driven approval routing.

athyper-api-runtime.name: content:sign:url
athyper-api-runtime.description: Generate secure signed URLs for content access.

athyper-api-runtime.name: runtime:admin
audit:write
athyper-api-runtime.description:
Write audit entries (used internally by runtime).
Usually assigned only to service accounts.

athyper-api-runtime.name: doc:write
athyper-api-runtime.description: Create, update, or modify document records and attachments.

athyper-api-runtime.name: base:auditor
athyper-api-runtime.description: Read + audit log access for compliance/reporting

athyper-api-runtime.name: mod:ACC:admin
athyper-api-runtime.description: Accounting module admin (editor-level)

athyper-api-runtime.name: mod:ACC:user
athyper-api-runtime.description: Accounting module user (operator-level)

athyper-api-runtime.name: content:write
athyper-api-runtime.description: Upload, update, or modify content records.

athyper-api-runtime.name: svc:worker
athyper-api-runtime.description: Background worker composite — timers, outbox, events, audit

athyper-api-runtime.name: wf:execute
athyper-api-runtime.description: Allows execution of workflow actions such as completing tasks or triggering transitions. Use cases: Approve/reject; Complete workflow step; Trigger next stage. Assigned to business users

athyper-api-runtime.name: outbox:read
athyper-api-runtime.description: Read pending outbox entries.

athyper-api-runtime.name: wf:timer:run
athyper-api-runtime.description:
Permission for automated timer workers to execute scheduled workflow events. Use cases: SLA escalation; 
Auto-approval timeout; Scheduled state transitions; Should only be assigned to athyper-svc-runtime-worker

athyper-api-runtime.name: event:publish
athyper-api-runtime.description:
Publish domain events into the platform event bus.
Used by services emitting domain events.

athyper-api-runtime.name: doc:sign:url
athyper-api-runtime.description: Generate secure signed URLs for document access (temporary download/upload links).  Use cases: Presigned S3/MinIO download; Controlled upload sessions; Typically granted to BFF service account, not users directly.

athyper-api-runtime.name: event:read
athyper-api-runtime.description: Consume published platform events.

athyper-api-runtime.name: content:read
athyper-api-runtime.description: Read access to stored content objects.

athyper-api-runtime.name: outbox:process
athyper-api-runtime.description:
Process and mark outbox events as dispatched.
Should only be granted to background worker service account

athyper-api-runtime.name: audit:read
athyper-api-runtime.description:
Read audit logs, permission decisions, integrity reports.
Restricted to compliance/admin roles.

athyper-api-runtime.name: mod:PAY:admin
athyper-api-runtime.description: Payments module admin (editor-level)

athyper-api-runtime.name: runtime:write
athyper-api-runtime.description:
Allows mutation of runtime-managed entities and state transitions (excluding administrative operations).
Use cases: Submit entity updates; Trigger lifecycle transitions; Modify runtime-managed records

athyper-api-runtime.name: base:editor
athyper-api-runtime.description: Write access + all operator permissions

athyper-api-runtime.name: content:overlay:apply
athyper-api-runtime.description: Apply metadata overlays or schema-driven modifications to content entities. Use cases: Meta-driven schema patching; Dynamic policy overlays; High privilege — usually admin/service role

athyper-api-runtime.name: runtime:invoke
athyper-api-runtime.description:
Allows invoking internal runtime services (commands, handlers, orchestrations) without broad write privileges.
Use cases: Service-to-service calls; Internal command execution; Controlled orchestration triggers. Ideal for BFF service accounts

athyper-api-runtime.name: wf:read
athyper-api-runtime.description: Read access to workflow definitions, instances, tasks, and history. Use cases: View approval status; View workflow timeline; Inspect workflow audit trail

athyper-api-runtime.name: doc:read
athyper-api-runtime.description: Read access to documents and metadata.
